[{"id":"VR871115","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">In the Bohr model for hydrogen atoms, two hydrogen atoms each have an electron in a circular orbit about the nucleus. In Atom <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span>, the electron’s orbital radius is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"r sub 1\"><math alttext=\"r sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span> and the atom is in energy state <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span>. In Atom <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>, the electron’s orbital radius is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"r sub 2\"><math alttext=\"r sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mstyle></math></span></span>, where <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"r sub 2 is greater than, r sub 1\"><math alttext=\"r sub 2 is greater than, r sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mstyle></math></span></span>, and the atom is in energy state <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>. Which of the following correctly compares the speeds of the two electrons and the potential energies of the two atoms?</p><div class=\"table_wrapper\"><table class=\"tgroup align:center cols:3 colsep:0 frame:none rowsep:0\"><col class=\"colspec colname:col1 colnum:1 colsep:1\"/><thead class=\"thead\"><tr class=\"row rowsep:1\"><th class=\"entry c